description: Planning permission for the redevelopment of the Grade II listed former St Clement's hospital site comprising the part demolition (and infill of associated basements), part refurbishment and change of use of the existing hospital buildings and the construction of eight new buildings between two and nine storeys high to accommodate 252 residential units, 306 sqm (GIA) community floorspace (D1 Use Class), 174 sq m (GIA) commercial floorspace (B1/A2 Use Class), 69sqm (GIA) caf?/restaurant (A3/A4 Use Class,) 32 parking spaces, cycle parking, refuse storage, plant equipment, private and communal amenity space and associated works.
